$ ctetra4_axial_force.bdf
$ Six CTETRA4 (Kuhn decomposition of unit cube) — axial extension in z
$
$ Geometry: 1 m × 1 m × 1 m cube, 6 tetrahedra (all positive volume)
$ Material: E = 1e6 Pa, nu = 0.3
$ Load:     1000 N total in +z on top face, applied as consistent nodal forces
$           Top face triangles: 5-6-7 and 5-7-8 (diagonal 5-7)
$           Each triangle area = 0.5 m², consistent load per node = 500/3 N
$           Nodes 5 and 7 appear in both triangles: F = 2*(500/3) = 333.333... N
$           Nodes 6 and 8 appear in one triangle each: F = 500/3 = 166.667... N
$ BCs:      fix T3 of all bottom-face nodes, fix T1+T2 of node 1, fix T2 of node 2
$
$ Hand calculation (CST is exact for linear axial field):
$   δ = F*L / (E*A) = 1000*1 / (1e6*1) = 1e-3 m
$   σ_z = F / A = 1000 Pa in every element
$
SOL 101
CEND
SUBCASE 1
  LABEL = CTETRA4 AXIAL FORCE
  LOAD = 1
  SPC = 1
  DISPLACEMENT = ALL
  STRESS = ALL
BEGIN BULK
PARAM,CSVOUT,YES
$ Nodes: unit cube
$ Bottom face (z=0): nodes 1-4
GRID,1,,0.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,2,,1.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,3,,1.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,4,,0.0,1.0,0.0
$ Top face (z=1): nodes 5-8
GRID,5,,0.0,0.0,1.0
GRID,6,,1.0,0.0,1.0
GRID,7,,1.0,1.0,1.0
GRID,8,,0.0,1.0,1.0
$ Material
MAT1,1,1.0E6,,0.3
$ Solid property
PSOLID,1,1
$ 6-tet Kuhn decomposition of unit cube (all positive determinant, V=1/6 each)
$ Main diagonal connects nodes 1 and 7
CTETRA,1,1,1,2,3,7
CTETRA,2,1,1,5,6,7
CTETRA,3,1,1,4,8,7
CTETRA,4,1,2,1,6,7
CTETRA,5,1,5,1,8,7
CTETRA,6,1,4,1,3,7
$ BCs: fix T3 of all bottom-face nodes (z=0)
SPC1,1,3,1
SPC1,1,3,2
SPC1,1,3,3
SPC1,1,3,4
$ Prevent lateral rigid body motion
SPC1,1,12,1
SPC1,1,2,2
$ Consistent nodal loads for uniform σ_z = 1000 Pa traction on top face
$ Top-face triangles: 5-6-7 (area=0.5) and 5-7-8 (area=0.5)
FORCE,1,5,0,333.3333333333333,0.0,0.0,1.0
FORCE,1,6,0,166.6666666666667,0.0,0.0,1.0
FORCE,1,7,0,333.3333333333333,0.0,0.0,1.0
FORCE,1,8,0,166.6666666666667,0.0,0.0,1.0
ENDDATA
